The paper discusses cognitive architectures for open-ended cognition, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed cognitive architecture involves the evolution of symbol structures in the brain, which is a concept that is closely related to neural networks and computational neuroscience (cs.NE). The paper also discusses systematicity, productivity, and compositionality, which are concepts that are relevant to computer science theory (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a new cognitive architecture, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
